</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8628475BFF808533FF13FE64FA5DFDBC" blockId="39.[136,1452,373,544]" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF808533FF13FE64FEE9FE28" bold="true" box="[189,294,410,436]" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">Notes:—</emphasis>
For years, this proliferous species remained unnoticed and misidentify as 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FF808533FBEAFE65FB01FE28" authorityName="Ames" authorityYear="1923" box="[1092,1230,410,436]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pleurothallis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="39" pageNumber="250" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scandens">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF808533FBEAFE65FB01FE28" box="[1092,1230,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">M. scandens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the only previously known proliferous species reported for 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFF808533FDE9FE40FD09FE44" box="[583,710,446,472]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FF808533FD7CFE40FC08FE44" authorityName="Pupulin, Bogarin &amp; Fernandez" authorityYear="2010" box="[722,967,446,472]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="39" pageNumber="250" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sotoanus">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF808533FD7CFE40FC08FE44" box="[722,967,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">Myoxanthus sotoanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recognized by linear leaves and flowers with brownish sepals, yellowish translucent petals and yellow lip. The most similar species is 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FF808533FB01FE1DFA9CFE60" authorityName="Rojas-Alvarado &amp; Karremans" authorityYear="2021" box="[1199,1363,483,508]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="39" pageNumber="250" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="panamense">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF808533FB01FE1DFA9CFE60" box="[1199,1363,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">M. panamense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FF808533FA23FE1DFF23FDBC" authorityName="Pupulin, Bogarin &amp; Fernandez" authorityYear="2010" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="39" pageNumber="250" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sotoanus">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF808533FA23FE1DFF23FDBC" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">M. sotoanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from the former by the brownish sepals 
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF808533FCC7FDF9FC4FFDBC" box="[873,896,519,544]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">vs</emphasis>
. greenish translucent and yellow lip 
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF808533FAB0FDF9FAFAFDBC" box="[1310,1333,519,544]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">vs</emphasis>
. purple.
</paragraph>
